Lifting Asian hair is a marathon, not a race!!! When I am lighting extremely dark hair I like to use @lorealpro #blondestudio9 with the bonder inside to make sure I keep the integrity of the hair while lifting it multiple levels! Also, when doing extremely dark hair- I choose to tone with more blue pigment to make sure I cancel out all unwanted orange pigment! 

Prep #metaldetox 
Lift #blondestudio9 
Tone #dialight 
Root melt- 5.01 
Mids and ends- 9.11
Styling products @lorealpro_education_us next day texture spray! 
Finish with the #metaldetox oil for that amazing shine and to seal the hair! 

#lorealproambassador #lorealpro #lorealprous @lorealpro_education_us @lorealpro

to achieve this look, I prepped her with @lorealpro Metal Detox! Arizona has tons of hard minerals in the water and this can cause unreliable color results. Behind my chair I run a really really tight schedule, so I need my clients to lift properly in order for my day to flow correctly. Let me tell you this stuff is a GAME CHANGER! I chose Blond studio 9 with the bonder inside to make sure the integrity of her hair stays intact while I am lifting it super light! Toned with #dialight 8.1 on the root and 10.01 on her ends! Finished with the new #metaldox oil to give it shine and protect against color fading! #lorealproambassador #lorealpro @lorealpro_education_us

I don’t always do hand paints…but when I do 👀 I use @lorealpro blond studio 9 with the bonder inside at a 1:1 ratio. I choose a 1:1 ratio because I really like a thicker consistency when I paint. With blonde studio 9 I get an amazing lift since it’s not a traditional clay lightener. To avoid the lightener running onto her drop out, I make sure to prep her hair correctly. This ensures that the hair is a clean canvas. In this case I prepped with #metaldetox to neutralize the metals in the hair so I get reliable color results. 🤝

Here’s a post that I didn’t think I was gonna make on here but idk here it is. I bought a house 🏡 Which is wild because I’m self employed so I really didn’t think I could to it by myself.. but I did and I am proud of myself for it. (Btw the rumors are true it’s fucking hard!!!!) I’ve been working since I was about 14/15 and grew up pretty fast. When I first started doing hair full time behind the chair my friends were having fun partying in college and I was worrying about if I could pay that weeks booth rent. It’s funny to me when I look back at that time; I used to feel so envious of other kids my age when I should’ve looked at what was right in front of me. Everyone’s life path is so extremely different and I’m thankful my life brought me here <3

Ps. This is a HORRIBLE photo and I look like an egg but it’s the only one I took so 🤐

Let’s talks ✨PRICES✨

Why don’t stylist have an exact price sheet?? ⬇️

I can’t speak for all stylist but here’s why I don’t have a price sheet.🗣️

A huge reason why hairdressers don’t have their prices blasted all over their page is because people want custom colors. 
Out are the day that people want chunky highlights, no toner and to leave wet…

People are wanting a beautiful blended balayage with intricate toners, and a heavy layered haircut. 

Now everyones hair is so customize to them that stylists really can’t have an exact price… 

For example, some people have a little bit of hair and some people have a lot… 
say someone with a TON of hair wants a full foil. The amount of product we use on them is going to be so different if you compare it to a full foil on someone that has a minimal amount of hair….👩🏻👩🏼👩🏽👩🏾👩🏿

It’s unfair for the clients and for us to charge the same on most services.

Curly hair talk 🗣️

Psa to all my people with curly/wavy hair! 
It’s normal to have different wave and curl patterns all over your head. Not many people have the same pattern everywhere. I know a lot of people with straight hair on the top of their head and curly hair around their nape. 

Embrace your different hair patterns. 

I personally don’t mind that my hair is pretty straight underneath and curly on top. If I’m getting an itch to make it look more uniform. I just run over it with a tiny curling iron and boom all symmetrical 💣

INSIDE LIGHT VS OUTSIDE LIGHT 💡 

same hair, same day, completely different tones ☀️

To everyone that gets their hair professionally colored understand that your hair is going to look completely different in different lights!!! Here’s why ⬇️
In warmer, yellowish light settings, your hair will reflect this color, resulting in a yellower tone; while in warmer, orange-based lights your hair will reflect a warmer, honey to brass color. Under cold white or blueish lights, your hair will appear to be more ash-blonde.

•Color correction transformation• 

Whenever a color correction sits in my chair I always know to prep with #metaldetox this removes unwanted metals from the hair. This ensures I get reliable color results and 87% less breakage. 

I always start by spraying in the pre-treatment and letting it dry for five minutes before starting. 
(Pro tip- this is a great time to get all your before videos in) 

After prepping my client, I went in with #bs9bi (it was extremely important that I went in with Blond Studio 9 Bonder Inside to protect the hair from breakage) 
I did a full tease light, not leaving any drop out and only teasing from the mid-shaft up. I proceeded to shampoo hair with metal detox. 

After my lightning portion was done I root melted her  with #dialight 7N & 7NB and 6vol 

I pre-toned her blue ends with #dialight 8GCand clear then applied 10VG and 9G with 6vol all over.
